                Text {
                    text: "&lt;h2 class=&quot;margin-top100&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;lead&quot;&gt;
	We create money for ourselves by taking a piece of paper and painting a nice picture on it.
	This picture then represents art and already has a value.
	This value can then be used to pay for services and also for goods, if the trading partner accepts them.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Each artist measures the number of minutes it takes to create this note and writes it on the respective artwork.
	This number of minutes is then immediately the value of the created note. 
	Suppose the artist needs half an hour, then he writes 30 on it.
	Then everyone knows that this note is worth 30 minutes. 
	Then when I give the artist a massage for which I need 90 minutes, I accept three of these notes as payment.
	To be honest, I would of course give this massage to friends for free, but it makes more fun and I 
	can use these notes to express my gratitude to someone else for their service.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Maybe you can use land to grow your own food and exchange it for LoveCoins.
	Or you own houses and accept LoveCoins as a rental.
&lt;/p&gt;"
